text: Homelix vittata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Per Olof Christopher Aurivillius in 1914, originally misspelled as "Homelix vittatus". It is known from Sierra Leone and the Ivory Coast.BioLib.cz - Homelix vittata. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. ==References== Category:Lamiinae Category:Beetles described in 1914
